{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2754a37b-1940-4f1f-86dd-9c26ca63686c","content":"Here's what you need:\n\n**Dockerfile changes:**\n\n```dockerfile\n# Create a writable dump directory accessible to your non-root user\nRUN mkdir -p /tmp/dumps && chown app:app /tmp/dumps\n\n# Configure CoreCLR to collect dumps on crash\nENV COMPlus_DbgEnableMiniDump=1\nENV COMPlus_DbgMiniDumpType=4\nENV COMPlus_DbgMiniDumpName=/tmp/dumps/coredump.%p.%t\n```\n\n`DbgMiniDumpType` values: `1` = Mini, `2` = Heap, `3` = Triage, `4` = Full.\n\n**docker run command:**\n\n```bash\ndocker run --cap-add=SYS_PTRACE -v /host/path/dumps:/tmp/dumps your-image\n```\n\n`--cap-add=SYS_PTRACE` is **required** — CoreCLR's `createdump` uses `ptrace` to snapshot the process. Without it, dump collection silently fails.\n\n**Notes:**\n- If on **.NET 7+**, use `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump` / `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType` / `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName` (the `COMPlus_` prefix still works but is deprecated).\n- The `-v` bind mount lets you retrieve dumps from the host after the container exits.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8c22806e-a5ca-4f0b-9b7d-3a5ddd4c3b2e","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to set up crash dump collection for a CoreCLR/.NET app in an Alpine-based Docker container running as a non-root user. I'll provide the Dockerfile changes and docker run command needed.\n\nKey considerations for Alpine + CoreCLR crash dumps:\n- Alpine uses musl libc, not glibc — createdump is the .NET tool for this\n- Need to set environment variables for CoreCLR dump collection\n- Need appropriate permissions since running as non-root\n- Need a writable dump directory\n- Need `ptrace` capability for createdump to work\n- SYS_PTRACE capability is needed at `docker run` time","outputTokens":515,"requestId":"9426:119996:180533A:1B5F173:69E81FFA"},"id":"c45a46a9-03f4-4bd1-af68-45f30751f812","timestamp":"2026-04-22T01:10:29.316Z","parentId":"9ee3d1e7-bd9a-46f3-9ce7-11a640d8d75a"}
